    dc:title "Redescription of the alpheid shrimp Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Alpheidae) from Peter the Great Bay, Russian coast of the Sea of Japan" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197838>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197834>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197835>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197836>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197837>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197839> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197838>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. a—Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950 (Alpheidae), adult male; b— burrowing decapods collected at the same site as B. levifrons: 1, 2 — Callianasa petalura Stimpson, 1860 (Callianassidae) (1 — female, 2 — male); 3 — Upogebia major (de Haan, 1841) (Upogebiidae) — the host for 4 — B. levifrons." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197838/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197834>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950, adult male (LEMMI) (above) and non-ovigerous adult female (NTOU M 00955) (below), habitus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197834/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197835>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950, adult male (LEMMI): a, b— frontal carapace and frontal appendages, dorsal; c— distal abdominal somites and telson, lateral; d— telson, dorsal; e, f— antennule, dorsal (e) and lateral (f); gantenna, dorsal; h— uropod, dorsal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197835/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197836>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950, adult male (LEMMI) a— mandible, mesial; b— maxillule, lateral; cmaxilla, lateral; d— first maxilliped, lateral; e, f— second maxilliped, lateral (e) and mesial (f); g— third maxilliped, lateral; h— same, distodorsal margin of antepenultimate segment and penultimate segment, mesial." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197836/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197837>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Betaeus levifrons Vinogradov, 1950, adult male (LEMMI): a, b— left cheliped, lateral (a) and mesial (b); csame, chela, lateral; d— second pereiopod, lateral; e— third pereiopod, lateral; f— fourth pereiopod, lateral; g— fifth pereiopod, lateral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197837/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.197839>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Currently known distribution of species of the genus Betaeus in the Sea of Japan and adjacent areas (based on Kubo, 1936; Yokoya, 1936; Vinogradov, 1950; Kim & Park, 1972; Miya, 1972; Kim, 1976; Yang et al., 2007; Nomura Komai, 2000); empty sign indicates the type locality of the species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/197839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

